<catsoop-section>Building the Minutes Counter</catsoop-section>

The minutes section is almost identical to seconds – two digits counting 00-59 with the same reset circuit.

### Minutes Assembly

```
1. On separate breadboard space, build another two-digit counter just like you did for seconds:
   - Two CD4026 ICs (units and tens)
   - Two 7-segment displays
   - Connect segments a-g from each IC to its display
   - Connect power, clock inhibit, and display enable for each IC
2. Connect the carry signal:
   - Units digit pin 5 (Carry Out) → tens digit pin 1 (Clock)
3. Add the diode reset circuit on tens digit:
   - Three 1N4148 diodes from segments e, f, g to reset pin
   - 10kΩ resistor from reset pin to GND
   - Connect both reset pins together
```

